The paper focuses on building behavior profiles of Android applications using multiple semantic views and representation learning techniques. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as the paper discusses malware detection and app clone detection. Additionally, the use of representation learning techniques and feature hashing suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions downstream analytics tasks such as app categorization and recommendation, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) respectively.
